      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1551814611,
      "post_id" : 1884902,
      "comment_id" : 96775473,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@sumanth232 A fail-fast iterator fails when <i>something else</i> modifies the container concurrently.  You are allowed to use the iterator as intended.  In this answer, nothing is modifying the key Set except for the iterator, and that is translated through to the Map owning that Set as well.  Only one operation per container is occurring at a time; no concurrency."
    } ],
