    "answer_id" : 1885385,
    "question_id" : 1884889,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>I agree with Paul Tomblin. I usually use the keyset's iterator, and then base my condition off the value for that key:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Iterator&lt;Integer&gt; it = map.keySet().iterator();\nwhile(it.hasNext()) {\n    Integer key = it.next();\n    Object val = map.get(key);\n    if (val.shouldBeRemoved()) {\n        it.remove();\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
