    "answer_id" : 25879686,
    "question_id" : 1884889,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>ConcurrentHashMap</strong></p>\n\n<p>You can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/ConcurrentHashMap.html\"><code>java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap</code></a>.</p>\n\n<p>It implements <code>ConcurrentMap</code> (which extends the <code>Map</code> interface).</p>\n\n<p><strong>E.g.</strong>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Map&lt;Object, Content&gt; map = new ConcurrentHashMap&lt;Object, Content&gt;();\n\nfor (Object key : map.keySet()) {\n    if (something) {\n        map.remove(key);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This approach leaves your code untouched. Only the <code>map</code> type differs.</p>\n"
  }, {
